The following concepts are considered: discounting and time value of the money; some securities (bond, stock, forward, future, swap, option); market of securities; mathematical models to price risk-free and risky future cash flows; pricing bonds, options etc; speculation, arbitrage, risk hedging and diversification at the market; portfolio theory, CAPM, APT.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The goal of the course is to give overview of the fundamental concepts of the financial markets and the basic models of the financial mathematics.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Student knows main types of financial markets and assets traded there, mathematical models of financial markets to price the risk-free and risky future cash flows.  Student has skills to find interests, net value of investment and investment portfolio risk, has skills to find prices of the bonds, options, futures etc, has skills to disperse and manage risks related with risky investments.
